President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Senator Max Baucus as the Ambassador to the People's Republic of China. Baucus has been working to strengthen the relationship between the US and China for over two decades, and his economic agreements have created jobs and added billions of dollars to the US economy. Baucus is currently the senior US Senator from Montana and has been serving in the Senate since 1978. He is also Chairman of the Senate Committee on Finance and a member of various other committees. Baucus previously served in the US House of Representatives and the Montana House of Representatives. He holds a B.A. and a J.D. from Stanford University.